💡 Automatic Light Control Using LDR
📌 Overview

This project demonstrates a sensor-based IoT simulation where an LED automatically turns ON/OFF based on light intensity using an LDR (Light Dependent Resistor).

🎯 Objective

To understand sensor-based automation

To simulate IoT systems using Tinkercad

To control LED using light intensity

⚙️ Components Used

Arduino UNO

LDR (Light Sensor)

LED

220Ω Resistor

10kΩ Resistor

Breadboard

🔌 Circuit Description

LDR connected to Analog Pin A0

LED connected to Digital Pin 9

Voltage divider used for LDR

💻 Code Functionality

Reads analog value from LDR

Maps value (0–1023 → 0–255)

Controls LED brightness using PWM

🔄 Working Principle

Low light → LED ON / Bright

High light → LED OFF / Dim

📊 Output

LED brightness varies based on light intensity

Sensor values visible in Serial Monitor

🚀 Applications

Smart street lights

Automatic home lighting

Energy-saving systems

📚 Conclusion

This project demonstrates how IoT sensors can automate systems and improve efficiency in real-world applications.
